Acacia dudgeoni

    Authority
      Family
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 11848

   Notes
   DESCRIPTION: Small tree or shrub with a spreading canopy, blackish,
   striated rough bark and reddish slash. Leaves bi-pinnate 3-7 cm long,
   with 20-30 pairs of leaflets. Flowers white, in racemes 2.5-6.0 cm
   long, shorter than the leaves. Fruit oblong, flattened, glabrous,
   3.0-8.0 x 1.5-2.5 cm, pale brown, papery. USE: Browsing, Service wood,
   Fuel wood, Charcoal, Fiber (roots), Medicine (anti diarrhetic), soil
   and land rehabilitation. GROWING PERIOD: Perennial. COMMON NAMES: Gum
   Arabic. FURTHER INF: Sudanian and Guinean ecozones, in relatively moist
   soil conditions in the southern Sahel (valleys floors, around ponds
   etc.). Found on medium to fine-textured soils.

   Sources
   [10]Grassland Index
   Steven R and Staberg P 2005

